      "observation": "step `upgrade_spring_boot_3_3` (jdk=17): BUILD FAILED post-recipe, rc=1\n--- first error cluster ---\n[03:52:38] PROJECT_ROOT=/work/src PHASE=build_post JDK=17\n[ERROR] COMPILATION ERROR : \n[ERROR] /work/src/GapsWeb/src/main/java/com/jasonhhouse/gaps/service/PlexQueryImpl.java:[20,42] error: package com.sun.org.apache.xml.internal.dtm.ref is not visible\n  (package com.sun.org.apache.xml.internal.dtm.ref is declared in module java.xml, which does not export it)\n[ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.apache.maven.plugins:maven-compiler-plugin:3.13.0:compile (default-compile) on project GapsWeb: Compilation failure\n[ERROR] /work/src/GapsWeb/src/main/java/com/jasonhhouse/gaps/service/PlexQueryImpl.java:[20,42] error: package com.sun.org.apache.xml.internal.dtm.ref is not visible\n[ERROR]   (package com.sun.org.apache.xml.internal.dtm.ref is declared in module java.xml, which does not export it)\n[ERROR] -> [Help 1]\n[ERROR] \n[ERROR] To see the full stack trace of the errors, re-run Maven with the -e switch.\n[ERROR] Re-run Maven using the -X switch to enable full debug logging.\n[ERROR] \n[ERROR] For more information about the errors and possible solutions, please read the following articles:\n[ERROR] [Help 1] http://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/MAVEN/MojoFailureException\n[ERROR] \n[ERROR] After correcting the problems, you can resume the build with the command\n[ERROR]   mvn <args> -rf :GapsWeb",
      "qwen_observation": "The build fails at `upgrade_spring_boot_3_3` because `PlexQueryImpl.java` imports `com.sun.org.apache.xml.internal.dtm.ref`, an internal JDK package that is not exported by default in JDK 17+. Previous attempts to add `--add-exports` via `maven.compiler.args` failed, likely because the property was not correctly wired into the `maven-compiler-plugin` configuration or the plugin version didn't support the property injection as expected.",
      "qwen_rationale": "Instead of relying on property injection which has failed twice, we will use a POM_PATCH step to directly modify the `maven-compiler-plugin` configuration in the POM. We will add the `--add-exports` argument directly to the `<compilerArgs>` list within the plugin configuration. This ensures the flag is passed to `javac` regardless of how the plugin is configured elsewhere. We also keep the `xalan` dependencies as they might be needed for other XML processing, but the critical fix is the direct compiler argument injection. We place this patch immediately before the Spring Boot upgrade step, which is where the failure occurs."
    },
